headline: 3 Top High-Yield Dividend Stocks I Just Bought in My Retirement Account
summary: While I like to see the passive income flow into my portfolio, that's not the main factor.  Dividend stocks have historically delivered more than double the total return of non-payers (9.2% annualized over the last 50 years versus 4.3%, according to data from Ned Davis Research and Hartford Funds).  The sweet spot has been companies that pay higher-yielding, steadily growing dividends.
